  <title>Other maintenance workflows</title>
  <info>
    <meta name="maintainer" content="tahlia.richardson@suse.com" its:translate="no"/>
  </info>
  <para>
    If you need a different workflow, or to perform a specific maintenance task, check the following list of articles:
  </para>

  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>General workflows</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          These articles describe general workflows for different scenarios:
        </para>
        <variablelist>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>
              <phrase condition="maint-cluster-infra">(This article)</phrase>
              <link xlink:href="https://documentation.suse.com/sle-ha/16.1/html/HA-maintenance-performing-tasks-cluster-infra/">
              <citetitle>Performing maintenance tasks on cluster infrastructure</citetitle></link>
            </term>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                This article describes how to perform cluster-wide maintenance tasks that don't require rebooting the nodes. In this scenario, &dlm; and &dlm;-dependent resources require downtime, but most other resources don't.
              </para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>
              <phrase condition="maint-cluster-nodes">(This article)</phrase>
              <link xlink:href="https://documentation.suse.com/sle-ha/16.1/html/HA-maintenance-performing-tasks-cluster-nodes/">
              <citetitle>Performing maintenance tasks on cluster nodes</citetitle></link>
            </term>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                This article describes how to perform maintenance tasks on one node at a time, whether rebooting or not rebooting. In this scenario, most resources don't require downtime because the cluster moves them to other nodes.
              </para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>
              <phrase condition="maint-cluster-resources">(This article)</phrase>
              <link xlink:href="https://documentation.suse.com/sle-ha/16.1/html/HA-maintenance-performing-tasks-cluster-resources/">
              <citetitle>Performing maintenance tasks on cluster resources</citetitle></link>
            </term>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                This article describes how to perform maintenance tasks on the resources managed by the cluster. In this scenario, the resources are placed in maintenance mode so you can manage them manually without any interference from the cluster.
              </para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
